\subsection{The eigenvalue of a Maass form}
\begin{definition}\label{mf.maass.mwf.eigenvalue}
\uses{mf.maass.mwf,mf.maass.mwf.laplacian,mf.maass.mwf.spectralparameter}
The **eigenvalue** $\lambda$ of a {{KNOWL('mf.maass.mwf', 'Maass newform')}} on GL(2) refers to the eigenvalue of the eigenspace of the {{ KNOWL('mf.maass.mwf.laplacian', "Laplace-Baltrami operator") }} in which it lies.

This eigenvalue is a real number that is typically written in the form $\lambda=\frac{1}{4}+R^2$, where $R$ is the {{KNOWL('mf.maass.mwf.spectralparameter', 'spectral parameter')}}.
\end{definition}


